What does the following PHP code output? 
<?php 
if (3 > 2) { 
echo 'Yes'; 
} else { 
echo 'No'; 
} 
?>

What will be the output of the following PHP code if no argument is passed to the function?

function makeCoffee($type = "Espresso") {
  return "Making a cup of $type";
}
echo makeCoffee();

What will be the output of the following PHP script if it is run as a standalone script? 

<?php
function test() {
    $x = 5;
    echo $x;
}
test();
echo $x;
?>

What will be the output of the following PHP code snippet? 

$array1 = array('a' => 'apple', 'b' => 'banana');
$array2 = array('a' => 'pear', 'b' => 'strawberry', 'c' => 'cherry');
$result = array_merge($array1, $array2);
print_r($result);

What will be the output of the following PHP code snippet?

<?php
function test() {
    $num = 10;
    function inner() {
        global $num;
        $num += 5;
    }
    inner();
    echo $num;
}
test();
?>
